findingsText:
 - analysis of a variety of commodities and artefacts that circulated in the early modern world;

- advacement of key methodologies in the analysis of global material culture;

- reflection on the way in which artefacts are used to construct global histories - use of the materials and methodologies in museum dislays, especially the future re-display of the V&amp;A and the Peabody Essex Museums.

- use of podcasts by schools and the general public.

- increasing standards of artefactual analysis by art dealers and the 'antique' sector. Education,Culture, Heritage, Museums and Collections
